item.title: The meaning of life, what's your opinion?
item.dc:creator: Insomniak
item.description:
λhlberg:

But I guess I can’t decide that myself since I’m not the one who created me.

Your DNA created you, and you are your DNA, thus you created you (though not through any decision of your own.) Your parents DNA created your DNA, and their parents DNA created theirs, and other prehistoric species had babies that evolved to create humans, et cetera. Sea-sponges, and primates, and eventually people had to fuck each other for millions of years to create you. Stars had to explode to create the matter you are made out of. Millions of animals had to be slaughtered and fed upon to create your ancestor’s bodies, out of which you eventually happened into existence.

The meaning of life? To put some serious thought into these strange happenings. Or perhaps nothing at all.

item.title: The meaning of life, what's your opinion?
item.dc:creator: Jethrosoup
item.description:
NetWarriorDan:

We long to be here for a purpose, even though, despite much self-deception, none is evident.

The significance of our lives and our fragile planet is then determined only by our own wisdom and courage. We are the custodians of life’s meaning.

If we crave some cosmic purpose, then let us find ourselves a worthy goal.

-Carl Sagan

item.title: The meaning of life, what's your opinion?
item.dc:creator: Kester
item.description:
Human life, and in fact all life is completely insignificant in terms of the universe, however it doesn’t mean each life is without purpose.

That purpose is simply for the species and life to procreate and continue it’s genome. If this wasn’t the case life would never have evolved and continued.

Every living things fights for survival for only one purpose, to procreate and continue it’s species. That, therefore, is the meaning of life.
